TITLE: Writing a Basic Jest Test Case
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code demonstrates a basic Jest test. It imports the `sum` function from `./sum.js` and defines a test case using the `test` function. Inside the test, `expect` and the `toBe` matcher are used to assert that calling `sum(1, 2)` results in `3`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.4/GettingStarted.md#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const sum = require('./sum');

test('adds 1 + 2 to equal 3', () => {
  expect(sum(1, 2)).toBe(3);
});
```

