TITLE: Using mockResolvedValue for async mocks (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: TypeScript implementation of mockResolvedValue showing how to create a properly typed mock function that returns a resolved Promise.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.6/MockFunctionAPI.md#2025-04-23_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import {jest, test} from '@jest/globals';

test('async test', async () => {
  const asyncMock = jest.fn<() => Promise<number>>().mockResolvedValue(43);

  await asyncMock(); // 43
});
```

