TITLE: Asserting Primitive Equality with `expect().toBe()` in Jest (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates a basic Jest test case using `expect()` with the `.toBe()` matcher to assert that the result of `bestLaCroixFlavor()` is strictly equal (using `Object.is`) to the string 'grapefruit'. Requires a Jest testing environment. Assumes `bestLaCroixFlavor()` is a function available in the test scope that returns a value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.4/ExpectAPI.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
test('the best flavor is grapefruit', () => {
  expect(bestLaCroixFlavor()).toBe('grapefruit');
});
```

