TITLE: Using Jest `.resolves` Matcher for Promise Testing
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows a more concise way to test a fulfilled promise using Jest's `.resolves` matcher. It asserts that the promise returned by `user.getUserName(5)` resolves, and that the resolved value is 'Paul'. The `expect` statement must be returned from the test.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.6/TutorialAsync.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
it('works with resolves', () => {
  expect.assertions(1);
  return expect(user.getUserName(5)).resolves.toBe('Paul');
});
```

