TITLE: Setting the Default Test Timeout in Jest using JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates changing the default timeout for all tests and hooks in the current test file with `jest.setTimeout`. By default, Jest uses a 5-second timeout; here, it is set to 1 second (1000 ms). Useful for enforcing shorter or longer test durations across an entire file, especially for performance-sensitive or slow environments. Parameter: timeout in milliseconds (here, `1000`). No dependencies besides Jest; this setting does not affect other files.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.5/JestObjectAPI.md#2025-04-23_snippet_31

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
jest.setTimeout(1000); // 1 second
```

