TITLE: Implementing Repeated Setup and Teardown Hooks in Jest (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the use of Jest\'s beforeEach and afterEach hooks for repeated test initialization and cleanup, particularly with a hypothetical city database. Each test runs with the database freshly set up and then cleaned. Requires custom methods like initializeCityDatabase, clearCityDatabase, and isCity defined elsewhere. Each test verifies the existence of a specified city, expecting a truthy result.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.7/SetupAndTeardown.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
beforeEach(() => {
  initializeCityDatabase();
});

afterEach(() => {
  clearCityDatabase();
});

test('city database has Vienna', () => {
  expect(isCity('Vienna')).toBeTruthy();
});

test('city database has San Juan', () => {
  expect(isCity('San Juan')).toBeTruthy();
});
```

