TITLE: Verifying Mock Function Call Count with expect.toHaveBeenCalledTimes
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates using the `toHaveBeenCalledTimes` matcher (alias `toBeCalledTimes`) in Jest to assert the exact number of times a mock function (`jest.fn()`) was called. This example tests a `drinkEach` function that should call the mock `drink` function twice.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.7/ExpectAPI.md#2025-04-23_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
test('drinkEach drinks each drink', () => {
  const drink = jest.fn();
  drinkEach(drink, ['lemon', 'octopus']);
  expect(drink).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(2);
});
```

