TITLE: Inspecting Jest Mock Function Calls and Instances in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet showcases the use of Jest's .mock property to access advanced information about how mock functions have been called, their contexts ('this'), and instances created via new. The example includes creating a mock constructor, binding contexts, and inspecting calls, making it especially relevant when verifying instance creation or context propagation in tests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.5/MockFunctions.md#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const myMock1 = jest.fn();
const a = new myMock1();
console.log(myMock1.mock.instances);
// > [ <a> ]

const myMock2 = jest.fn();
const b = {};
const bound = myMock2.bind(b);
bound();
console.log(myMock2.mock.contexts);
// > [ <b> ]
```

