TITLE: Mocking Axios Module Dependencies in Jest Tests (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This Jest test demonstrates how to mock the `axios` module to test the `Users.all` method without making actual HTTP requests. `jest.mock('axios')` replaces `axios` with a mock. Then, `axios.get.mockResolvedValue(resp)` configures the mocked `get` method to return a predefined successful promise. The test verifies that `Users.all()` returns the expected data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.4/MockFunctions.md#2025-04-23_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import axios from 'axios';
import Users from './users';

jest.mock('axios');

test('should fetch users', () => {
  const users = [{name: 'Bob'}];
  const resp = {data: users};
  axios.get.mockResolvedValue(resp);

  // or you could use the following depending on your use case:
  // axios.get.mockImplementation(() => Promise.resolve(resp))

  return Users.all().then(data => expect(data).toEqual(users));
});
```

