TITLE: Asserting Jest Mock Calls and Results in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet provides examples for asserting various mock properties after calls in Jest: call counts, argument matching, instance analysis, and verifying return values and contexts. It showcases granular matchers for mock calls, the use of .mock.instances, .mock.results, and .mock.lastCall. Meant for use inside a Jest test suite, it assumes a mock function under test (someMockFunction) and other relevant test objects.
