TITLE: Testing Asynchronous Callbacks with Jest - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the correct way to test asynchronous code that uses callbacks instead of promises. It demonstrates using the 'done' parameter in Jest, which the test must call to signal completion. Errors within the callback are caught and passed to done to ensure proper error logging in Jest. Dependencies are Jest and a callback-based fetchData.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.7/TestingAsyncCode.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
test('the data is peanut butter', done => {
  function callback(error, data) {
    if (error) {
      done(error);
      return;
    }
    try {
      expect(data).toBe('peanut butter');
      done();
    } catch (error) {
      done(error);
    }
  }

  fetchData(callback);
});
```

