TITLE: Scoping Jest Setup/Teardown Hooks within Describe Blocks (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how Jest hooks (`beforeEach` in this example) can be scoped. Hooks defined at the top level apply to all tests in the file, while hooks defined inside a `describe` block apply only to the tests within that specific block. This allows for different setup procedures for different groups of tests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.6/SetupAndTeardown.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
// Applies to all tests in this file
beforeEach(() => {
  return initializeCityDatabase();
});

test('city database has Vienna', () => {
  expect(isCity('Vienna')).toBeTruthy();
});

test('city database has San Juan', () => {
  expect(isCity('San Juan')).toBeTruthy();
});

describe('matching cities to foods', () => {
  // Applies only to tests in this describe block
  beforeEach(() => {
    return initializeFoodDatabase();
  });

  test('Vienna <3 veal', () => {
    expect(isValidCityFoodPair('Vienna', 'Wiener Schnitzel')).toBe(true);
  });

  test('San Juan <3 plantains', () => {
    expect(isValidCityFoodPair('San Juan', 'Mofongo')).toBe(true);
  });
});
```

