TITLE: Using beforeEach for Per-Test Setup in Jest (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the `beforeEach` hook in Jest. It runs an asynchronous setup function (clearing and inserting data into a database) before each test in the file. Jest waits for the promise to resolve before starting the test, ensuring a clean state for every test case.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.4/GlobalAPI.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
