TITLE: Skipping Data-Driven Test Suites with describe.skip.each (Array Table) in Jest (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to use describe.skip.each with an array of input arrays to skip data-driven test suites in Jest. Structures provided in the skip block are ignored during execution. Dependencies include Jest; the input is a table array and only tests outside the skipped suites are run.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.6/GlobalAPI.md#2025-04-23_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
describe.skip.each([
  [1, 1, 2],
  [1, 2, 3],
  [2, 1, 3],
])('.add(%i, %i)', (a, b, expected) => {
  test(`returns ${expected}`, () => {
    expect(a + b).toBe(expected); // will not be run
  });
});

test('will be run', () => {
  expect(1 / 0).toBe(Infinity);
});
```

