TITLE: Implementing CheckboxWithLabel Component (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: A React functional component `CheckboxWithLabel`. It renders a checkbox input within a label. The label text changes between `labelOn` and `labelOff` props based on the checkbox's checked state, managed using the `useState` hook.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.4/TutorialReact.md#2025-04-23_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import {useState} from 'react';

export default function CheckboxWithLabel({labelOn, labelOff}) {
  const [isChecked, setIsChecked] = useState(false);

  const onChange = () => {
    setIsChecked(!isChecked);
  };

  return (
    <label>
      <input type="checkbox" checked={isChecked} onChange={onChange} />
      {isChecked ? labelOn : labelOff}
    </label>
  );
}
```

