TITLE: Using a Manual Mock in Jest Tests - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to import and use manual mocks in Jest test files. It demonstrates clearing mock state before each test and verifying constructor and method invocations using Jest's matcher functions. Assumes the mock is exported from __mocks__/sound-player.js and that Jest's automocking is in place for ./sound-player.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.6/Es6ClassMocks.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
