TITLE: Defining an Infinite Recursive Timer-based Game Module in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Implements a function that prints a start message, sets a 1-second timeout after which it prints another message, invokes a callback, and then recursively schedules another game after 10 seconds. The recursion supports infinite games via timers. No external dependencies required except for Node.js. It is suitable for demonstrating complex timer scenarios and recursive timing logic.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.6/TimerMocks.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
function infiniteTimerGame(callback) {
  console.log('Ready....go!');

  setTimeout(() => {
    console.log("Time's up! 10 seconds before the next game starts...");
    callback && callback();

    // Schedule the next game in 10 seconds
    setTimeout(() => {
      infiniteTimerGame(callback);
    }, 10000);
  }, 1000);
}

module.exports = infiniteTimerGame;
```

