TITLE: Testing Last Return Value of Mock Functions with toHaveLastReturnedWith in Jest
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the toHaveLastReturnedWith matcher to test the specific value that a mock function last returned. The example creates a mock function that returns beverage names and verifies the last returned value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.5/ExpectAPI.md#2025-04-23_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
test('drink returns La Croix (Orange) last', () => {
  const beverage1 = {name: 'La Croix (Lemon)'};
  const beverage2 = {name: 'La Croix (Orange)'};
  const drink = jest.fn(beverage => beverage.name);

  drink(beverage1);
  drink(beverage2);

  expect(drink).toHaveLastReturnedWith('La Croix (Orange)');
});
```

