TITLE: Comparing Numbers with Various Matchers in Jest
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use different number comparison matchers in Jest, including toBeGreaterThan, toBeGreaterThanOrEqual, toBeLessThan, toBeLessThanOrEqual, toBe, and toEqual for numbers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/docs/UsingMatchers.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
test('two plus two', () => {
  const value = 2 + 2;
  expect(value).toBeGreaterThan(3);
