TITLE: Creating a Custom Jest Transformer using @babel/core
DESCRIPTION: Defines a custom Jest transformer (`custom-transformer.js`) using `@babel/core` directly. It exports a `process` function that takes source code (`src`) and filename, transforms it using `@babel/core` with the `babel-preset-jest` preset, and returns the transformed code. Requires installing `@babel/core` and `babel-preset-jest`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.6/TutorialReact.md#2025-04-23_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
'use strict';

const {transform} = require('@babel/core');
const jestPreset = require('babel-preset-jest');

module.exports = {
  process(src, filename) {
    const result = transform(src, {
      filename,
      presets: [jestPreset],
    });

    return result || src;
  },
};
```

