TITLE: JavaScript Volume Class Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Defines a Volume class with custom equality logic for comparing volumes in different units (L and mL).
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.4/ExpectAPI.md#2025-04-23_snippet_47

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export class Volume {
  constructor(amount, unit) {
    this.amount = amount;
    this.unit = unit;
  }

  toString() {
    return `[Volume ${this.amount}${this.unit}]`;
  }

  equals(other) {
    if (this.unit === other.unit) {
      return this.amount === other.amount;
    } else if (this.unit === 'L' && other.unit === 'mL') {
      return this.amount * 1000 === other.unit;
    } else {
      return this.amount === other.unit * 1000;
    }
  }
}
```

