TITLE: Defining a Recursive Timer Function in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a JavaScript function `infiniteTimerGame` that uses nested `setTimeout` calls to create a recursive timer. After an initial 1-second delay, it calls the provided callback and then schedules itself to run again after a 10-second delay. The function is exported using `module.exports`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.4/TimerMocks.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function infiniteTimerGame(callback) {
  console.log('Ready....go!');

  setTimeout(() => {
    console.log("Time's up! 10 seconds before the next game starts...");
    callback && callback();

    // Schedule the next game in 10 seconds
    setTimeout(() => {
      infiniteTimerGame(callback);
    }, 10000);
  }, 1000);
}

module.exports = infiniteTimerGame;
```

