TITLE: Focusing Parameterized Test Suites with `each`.describe.only in Jest (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use `.describe.only` (or alias `.fdescribe`) with Jest's `each` and tagged template literals. This focuses the test runner exclusively on the parameterized test suite generated by this `each` block, skipping all other `describe` blocks and top-level tests. The data definition and suite function structure remain the same.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/packages/jest-each/README.md#2025-04-23_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
each`
  a    | b    | expected
  ${1} | ${1} | ${2}
  ${1} | ${2} | ${3}
  ${2} | ${1} | ${3}
`.describe.only('$a + $b', ({a, b, expected}) => {
  test(`returns ${expected}`, () => {
    expect(a + b).toBe(expected);
  });
});
```

