TITLE: Implementing a Recursive Timer Game Function in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: A function that uses recursive setTimeout calls to create a repeating timer. This is a common pattern for implementing game loops or periodic background tasks that need to be tested.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/docs/TimerMocks.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function infiniteTimerGame(callback) {
  console.log('Ready....go!');

  setTimeout(() => {
    console.log("Time's up! 10 seconds before the next game starts...");
    callback && callback();

    // Schedule the next game in 10 seconds
    setTimeout(() => {
      infiniteTimerGame(callback);
    }, 10000);
  }, 1000);
}

module.exports = infiniteTimerGame;
```

