TITLE: Modifying Jest Mocks with mockImplementation in JavaScript Tests
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to change the behavior of an existing Jest mock dynamically within a test suite. After initially mocking `SoundPlayer` with `jest.mock`, `SoundPlayer.mockImplementation()` is called inside a `beforeAll` block to provide a specific implementation for the tests within that `describe` block. In this case, the `playSoundFile` method is reimplemented to throw an error, allowing testing of error handling in `SoundPlayerConsumer`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.4/Es6ClassMocks.md#2025-04-23_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
```javascript
import SoundPlayer from './sound-player';
import SoundPlayerConsumer from './sound-player-consumer';

jest.mock('./sound-player');

describe('When SoundPlayer throws an error', () => {
  beforeAll(() => {
    SoundPlayer.mockImplementation(() => {
      return {
        playSoundFile: () => {
          throw new Error('Test error');
        },
      };
    });
  });

  it('Should throw an error when calling playSomethingCool', () => {
    const soundPlayerConsumer = new SoundPlayerConsumer();
    expect(() => soundPlayerConsumer.playSomethingCool()).toThrow();
  });
});
```
```

