TITLE: Parallelizing Tasks with jest-worker in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates using `jest-worker` for task parallelization. It defines a worker module (`heavy-task.js`) exporting a potentially long-running function. The main script (`main.js`) imports the `Worker` class from `jest-worker`, creates a worker instance pointing to the task module, and then invokes the exported function (`myHeavyTask`) concurrently with different arguments using `Promise.all`. This allows CPU-intensive tasks to run in separate processes, improving performance. Requires the `jest-worker` package.
