TITLE: Implementing a Cached Task in a JestWorker Child Process using Babel in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This worker module (`worker.js`) defines an asynchronous `transform` function using Babel to transform files. It maintains an in-memory `cache` specific to this worker instance. When called via a `jest-worker` configured with `computeWorkerKey` (using filename), subsequent calls for the same file are routed to this worker and served from the cache, demonstrating stateful behavior. Requires the `@babel/core` package.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/packages/jest-worker/README.md#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import babel from '@babel/core';

const cache = Object.create(null);

export function transform(filename) {
  if (cache[filename]) {
    return cache[filename];
  }

  // jest-worker can handle both immediate results and thenables. If a
  // thenable is returned, it will be await'ed until it resolves.
  return babel.transformFileAsync(filename).then(result => {
    cache[filename] = result;

    return result;
  });
}
```

