TITLE: Skipping Concurrent Data-Driven Tests Using Jest (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Applies the `test.concurrent.skip.each` API to prevent a collection of concurrent, data-driven tests from running while allowing other tests to execute. The skipped tests are declared in a table, but only the non-skipped test executes. Intended for use when temporarily disabling tests; requires Jest with concurrent test capability. Each row defines a test case, but the callback for these tests will not run.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.6/GlobalAPI.md#2025-04-23_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
test.concurrent.skip.each([
  [1, 1, 2],
  [1, 2, 3],
  [2, 1, 3],
])('.add(%i, %i)', async (a, b, expected) => {
  expect(a + b).toBe(expected); // will not be run
});

test('will be run', () => {
  expect(1 / 0).toBe(Infinity);
});
```

