TITLE: Creating and Registering a Custom Equality Tester in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines a typed function `areVolumesEqual` in TypeScript as a custom equality tester for `Volume` instances. It checks types using `instanceof` and delegates comparison to the `Volume.equals` method or returns `undefined`/`false` based on type compatibility. It registers the tester using `expect.addEqualityTesters`. Requires the `Volume` class and `@jest/globals`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.5/ExpectAPI.md#2025-04-23_snippet_55

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
import {expect} from '@jest/globals';
import {Volume} from './Volume.js'; // Assuming Volume.ts is compiled to Volume.js

function areVolumesEqual(a: unknown, b: unknown): boolean | undefined {
  const isAVolume = a instanceof Volume;
  const isBVolume = b instanceof Volume;

  if (isAVolume && isBVolume) {
    return a.equals(b);
  } else if (isAVolume === isBVolume) {
    // Let Jest's default equality testers handle comparison of non-Volumes or two Volumes
    return undefined;
  } else {
    // If one is a Volume and the other isn't, they're not equal
    return false;
  }
}

expect.addEqualityTesters([areVolumesEqual]);
```

