TITLE: Asserting Calls and Results of Jest Mocks in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates various assertions on calls, arguments, return values, contexts, and instances using the .mock property within Jest. This snippet is dependency-free except for Jest, and is intended for use within test files to ensure mock behaviors conform to expectations. Assumes 'someMockFunction' and 'element' are defined in the test context.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.5/MockFunctions.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
