TITLE: Example Jest Test with Manual Puppeteer Setup (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Shows an example test (`test.js`) utilizing the manual Puppeteer setup. It accesses the browser instance via `globalThis.__BROWSER_GLOBAL__` (made available by the custom environment), creates a new page, navigates to Google, and checks the body text content. A timeout is configured for the asynchronous operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.7/Puppeteer.md#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// test.js
const timeout = 5000;

describe(
  '/ (Home Page)',
  () => {
    let page;
    beforeAll(async () => {
      page = await globalThis.__BROWSER_GLOBAL__.newPage();
      await page.goto('https://google.com');
    }, timeout);

    it('should load without error', async () => {
      const text = await page.evaluate(() => document.body.textContent);
      expect(text).toContain('google');
    });
  },
  timeout,
);
```

