TITLE: Summarizing Files in a Directory with the fs Module - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript module defines a utility function that synchronously summarizes files in a directory using Node's fs module. It exports a function that returns an array of objects with directory and fileName properties, depending on the output of fs.readdirSync. Requires Node.js and access to the 'fs' core module as a dependency.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.5/ManualMocks.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
'use strict';\n\nconst fs = require('fs');\n\nfunction summarizeFilesInDirectorySync(directory) {\n  return fs.readdirSync(directory).map(fileName => ({\n    directory,\n    fileName,\n  }));\n}\n\nexports.summarizeFilesInDirectorySync = summarizeFilesInDirectorySync;\n
```

