TITLE: Configuring transformIgnorePatterns for pnpm Package Manager in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Advanced example showing how to configure transformIgnorePatterns to work with pnpm package manager, handling its unique symlink structure to correctly transform specific packages under node_modules.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.5/Configuration.md#2025-04-23_snippet_93

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
/** @type {import('jest').Config} */
const config = {
  transformIgnorePatterns: [
    '<rootDir>/node_modules/.pnpm/(?!(package-a|@scope\\+pkg-b)@)',
    /* if config file is under '~/packages/lib-a/' */
    `${path.join(
      __dirname,
      '../..',
    )}/node_modules/.pnpm/(?!(package-a|@scope\\+pkg-b)@)`,
    /* or using relative pattern to match the second 'node_modules/' in 'node_modules/.pnpm/@scope+pkg-b@x.x.x/node_modules/@scope/pkg-b/' */
    'node_modules/(?!.pnpm|package-a|@scope/pkg-b)',
  ],
};

module.exports = config;
```

