TITLE: Creating a Custom Jest Transformer Using @babel/core
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to build a custom transformer for Jest using @babel/core and babel-preset-jest. The transformer processes JavaScript source files through Babel with the Jest preset applied.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.4/TutorialReact.md#2025-04-23_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
'use strict';

const {transform} = require('@babel/core');
const jestPreset = require('babel-preset-jest');

module.exports = {
  process(src, filename) {
    const result = transform(src, {
      filename,
      presets: [jestPreset],
    });

    return result || src;
  },
};
```

