SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.7/TestingAsyncCode.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
test('the data is peanut butter', async () => {
  const data = await fetchData();
  expect(data).toBe('peanut butter');
});

test('the fetch fails with an error', async () => {
  expect.assertions(1);
  try {
    await fetchData();
  } catch (error) {
    expect(error).toMatch('error');
  }
});
```

