TITLE: Using jest.doMock with Dynamic ES6 Imports (JS)
DESCRIPTION: Explains how to use `jest.doMock` with ES6 modules when avoiding `require`. This involves using dynamic `import()` calls (since static imports are hoisted before `doMock` can run), setting `__esModule: true` in the mock factory, and ensuring the environment supports dynamic imports (e.g., via Babel plugins like `babel-plugin-dynamic-import-node`).
