TITLE: Filtering Test Suites with shouldRunTestSuite Hook (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates two ways to use the `shouldRunTestSuite` hook in Jest--synchronously and asynchronously. The hook takes a `testSuiteInfo` parameter, allowing the plugin to control which test suites run based on conditions such as the file path. Usage of synchronous return (`boolean`) or an asynchronous `Promise<boolean>` is supported, and the plugin may selectively execute suites containing a custom keyword.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.4/WatchPlugins.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class MyWatchPlugin {
  apply(jestHooks) {
    jestHooks.shouldRunTestSuite(testSuiteInfo => {
      return testSuiteInfo.testPath.includes('my-keyword');
    });

    // or a promise
    jestHooks.shouldRunTestSuite(testSuiteInfo => {
      return Promise.resolve(testSuiteInfo.testPath.includes('my-keyword'));
    });
  }
}
```

