TITLE: Handling Jest Module Resets with beforeEach in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates a pattern to handle Jest's behavior of resetting the module registry after each test (`it` block). The `require` statement for the 'sum' module is placed inside a `beforeEach` block to ensure a fresh copy of the module is loaded before each test runs, maintaining test isolation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/blog/2016-03-11-javascript-unit-testing-performance.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
```js
let sum;
describe('sum', () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    sum = require('sum');
  });
  it('works', () => {
    expect(sum(5, 4)).toBe(9);
  });
  it('works too', () => {
    // This copy of sum is not the same as in the previous call to `it`.
    expect(sum(2, 3)).toBe(5);
  });
});
```
```

