TITLE: Implementing Global Teardown for Manual Puppeteer Integration (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Defines a Jest global teardown script (`teardown.js`). It accesses the browser instance stored in `globalThis.__BROWSER_GLOBAL__` by the setup script and calls `close()` to terminate the Puppeteer browser. It also removes the temporary directory containing the WebSocket endpoint file. Requires `fs.promises`, `os`, and `path` modules.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.5/Puppeteer.md#2025-04-23_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// teardown.js
const fs = require('fs').promises;
const os = require('os');
const path = require('path');

const DIR = path.join(os.tmpdir(), 'jest_puppeteer_global_setup');
module.exports = async function () {
  // close the browser instance
  await globalThis.__BROWSER_GLOBAL__.close();

  // clean-up the wsEndpoint file
  await fs.rm(DIR, {recursive: true, force: true});
};
```

