TITLE: Mocking ES6 Modules with Default and Named Exports in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates mocking an ES6 module with both default and named exports using jest.mock. The factory returns an object with __esModule set to true and mock implementations for 'default' and 'foo'. This ensures correct import behavior (default and named). Requires Babel or TypeScript for native ES module handling; manual __esModule property may be necessary.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/docs/JestObjectAPI.md#2025-04-23_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import moduleName, {foo} from '../moduleName';

jest.mock('../moduleName', () => {
  return {
    __esModule: true,
    default: jest.fn(() => 42),
    foo: jest.fn(() => 43),
  };
});

moduleName(); // Will return 42
foo(); // Will return 43
```

