TITLE: Using expect.arrayContaining() in Jest for Subset Checks
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates Jest's `expect.arrayContaining(array)` matcher within a `describe` block. It asserts that the received array contains all elements of the expected array (subset check), allowing for additional elements in the received array. It also shows a negative test case where the received array is missing an expected element.
