TITLE: Correctly Testing Callbacks with `done` in Jest (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the correct way to test asynchronous code using callbacks in Jest. The test function accepts a `done` argument. Jest waits until `done()` is explicitly called within the callback to finish the test. Error handling is included using `try...catch` to pass potential assertion errors to `done(error)`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.4/TestingAsyncCode.md#2025-04-23_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
test('the data is peanut butter', done => {
  function callback(error, data) {
    if (error) {
      done(error);
      return;
    }
    try {
      expect(data).toBe('peanut butter');
      done();
    } catch (error) {
      done(error);
    }
  }

  fetchData(callback);
});
```

