TITLE: Defining a Custom Volume Class in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines a simple `Volume` class in JavaScript with `amount` and `unit` properties, a `toString` method, and an `equals` method for comparing volume instances, potentially with different units ('L' and 'mL'). This class is used to demonstrate custom equality testers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-29.5/ExpectAPI.md#2025-04-23_snippet_51

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
// For simplicity in this example, we'll just support the units 'L' and 'mL'
export class Volume {
  constructor(amount, unit) {
    this.amount = amount;
    this.unit = unit;
  }

  toString() {
    return `[Volume ${this.amount}${this.unit}]`;
  }

  equals(other) {
    if (this.unit === other.unit) {
      return this.amount === other.amount;
    } else if (this.unit === 'L' && other.unit === 'mL') {
      return this.amount * 1000 === other.unit; // Note: Original code has a potential typo here (other.unit instead of other.amount)
    } else {
      return this.amount === other.unit * 1000; // Note: Original code has a potential typo here (other.unit instead of other.amount)
    }
  }
}
```

